You are a senior full-stack software architect.



Build a complete END-TO-END full stack project named

"Online Medication & Prescription Tracker"

using industry best practices.



=====================

TECH STACK

=====================

Frontend:

- React (Vite)

- React Router

- Axios

- Simple clean UI (no heavy styling)



Backend:

- Java 17

- Spring Boot 3

- Spring Security (JWT based authentication)

- REST APIs



Database:

- MySQL (structured relational data only)



=====================

USER ROLES

=====================

1. Doctor

2. Patient

3. Admin (basic)



=====================

AUTHENTICATION FLOW

=====================

- Common Register and Login for all users

- User selects role during registration

- JWT based authentication

- Role-based dashboard redirection



=====================

DOCTOR FLOW

=====================

After login, Doctor should:

1. Complete doctor profile (specialization, hospital, experience)

2. View list of assigned patients

3. Create prescription for a patient

4. Add medicines with:

   - Medicine name

   - Dosage

   - Frequency (Morning / Afternoon / Night)

   - Duration (number of days)

5. System should auto-generate medication schedule

6. View patient medication intake status:

   - DONE

   - PENDING

   - MISSED



=====================

PATIENT FLOW

=====================

After login, Patient should:

1. View assigned doctor(s)

2. View prescriptions

3. View today's medication reminders

4. Click DONE after taking medicine

5. Intake status should update in doctor dashboard



=====================

ADMIN FLOW

=====================

Admin can:

1. Login

2. Verify doctor accounts

3. View basic system statistics



